Package: bcnma
Title: Bayesian Component Network Meta-Analysis with LASSO Interactions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yuki", "Furukawa",
        email   = "furukawa.y.psy@gmail.com",
        role    = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Orestis", "Efthimiou",
        role    = "ths",
        comment = "Conceptual guidance on Bayesian cNMA and SSVS modelling"))
Description: Fits Bayesian random-effects component network meta-analysis (cNMA)
    for binary outcomes using JAGS. Supports three interaction models: fully
    additive (no interactions), spike-and-slab SSVS with equiprobable priors
    (LASSO), and SSVS with informative priors for selected component pairs
    (lasso_informative). Provides S3 methods for printing, forest plots, and
    interaction summaries, plus a combination-comparison function that propagates
    posterior uncertainty through both main effects and interaction terms.
    The package was developed by packaging and generalising analysis scripts
    originally written for the CBT-I Component NMA project (Furukawa et al.
    2024, JAMA Psychiatry). Designed to feel familiar to users of the
    netmeta/meta ecosystem.
